        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3383429189" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4853325912455356438">&quot;I, John Brown, am now quite certain that the crimes of this guilty land can never be purged away but with blood.&quot;<br/><br/>John Brown was a fascinating man, and he truly was the catalyst for civil war in America. Tension had been brewing for decades, but Brown&apos;s series of rabid anti-slavery attacks and raids between 1854-1859, culminating with his raid on Harpers Ferry, were ultimately the tipping point. Horwitz does a fantastic job showing how Brown was at the center of it all, from the events in the ye</span>
  <span id="freeText4853325912455356438" style="display:none">"I, John Brown, am now quite certain that the crimes of this guilty land can never be purged away but with blood."<br /><br />John Brown was a fascinating man, and he truly was the catalyst for civil war in America. Tension had been brewing for decades, but Brown's series of rabid anti-slavery attacks and raids between 1854-1859, culminating with his raid on Harpers Ferry, were ultimately the tipping point. Horwitz does a fantastic job showing how Brown was at the center of it all, from the events in the years leading up to Harpers Ferry to the aftermath of his capture and hanging. </span>
